### d. Cash flow to Creditors and Cash flow to Shareholders

Cash Flow to Creditors is computed as follows:

$$\begin{aligned} \text{Cash Flow to Creditors} &= \text{Interest Paid} - {\text{Net New Borrowings}}\\[5pt] 
&= \text{\$2,650} - {\text{0}}\\[5pt]
&= \underline{\underline{\textbf{\$2,650}}} 
\end{aligned}

Now that we have computed the cash flow from assets and cash flow to creditors, let's now compute for the cash flow to shareholders by squeezing back of cash flow from assets.

$$\begin{aligned} \text{Cash Flow to Shareholders} &= \text{Cash flow from Assets} - {\text{Cash Flow to Creditors}}\\[5pt] 
&= \text{- \$2,166} - {\text{2,650}}\\[5pt] 
&= \underline{\underline{\textbf{(\$ 4,816)}}} 
\end{aligned}
